# bin/.scrub-extra-patterns.example
#
# Copy to bin/.scrub-extra-patterns (gitignored) and list operator-specific
# EXACT values you never want to appear in this PUBLIC repo. scrub-check.sh
# loads these at runtime and scans for them alongside the built-in patterns, so
# the public script itself never has to hardcode the sensitive values.
#
# Format: one POSIX extended-regex per line. Blank lines and '#' comments ignored.
# Override the file location with the ALFRED_SCRUB_EXTRA_PATTERNS env var.
#
# Examples (uncomment + replace with your real values):
# (^|[^0-9])123456789012([^0-9]|$)      # your AWS account ID (an identifier, not a secret, but keep it private)
# myco-internal\.example\.com            # a private hostname
# #your-private-slack-channel            # a private Slack channel name
